    "explanation": "<p>Mean of the five observations,</p>\n<p>$$\\mu=\\frac{80.0+80.5+81.0+81.5+82}{5}=\\frac{405.0}{5}=81$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Mean error</p>\n<p>$$=\\frac{|80-\\mu|+|80.5-\\mu|+|81.0-\\mu|+|81.5-\\mu| +|82-\\mu|}{5}$$</p>\n<p>$$=\\frac{|80-81|+|80.5-81|+|81.0-81| +|81.5-81|+|82-81|}{5}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{gathered}\n=\\frac{1+0.5+0+0.5+1}{5}=\\frac{3}{5}=0.6 \\\\\n\\therefore \\quad \\text { Mean % error }=\\frac{0.6}{81} \\times 100 \\%=0.74 \\%\n\\end{gathered}$$</p>",
